column68: Received Silver Award for the research paper at SLIIT research symposium in 2016. -The concept of the research is to develop a prediction model to forecast water quality relative to pH, dissolved oxygen, turbidity and conductivity (Artificial Neural Network and ARIMA model)   	The improvements in computational power tended prediction based research to focus on Artificial Neural Network (ANN). Even though conventional algorithms handled similar tasks, a higher tenancy on applying ANN can be seen.   	We test the improvement on prediction over a conventional algorithm. We use ANN and ARIMA on small time series datasets.  	 Results generated through both the algorithms are compared with each other to see the improvement. The result that which were generated reveals that for a small dataset the conventional algorithms hold a higher accuracy rate than the ANN.  	Research was completed successfully with A- grade.
